## 5. Command/Action Injection

### Architecture: MessageStream → CommandList → GameLogic

The flow is:
1. Input events (keyboard/mouse/AI) are appended to `TheMessageStream`
2. `TheMessageStream->propagateMessages()` runs all attached `GameMessageTranslator`s in priority order
3. Translated commands fall through to `TheCommandList` (the final translator)
4. At the start of `TheGameLogic->update()`, `processCommandList(TheCommandList)` executes them

### GameMessage (`/GameEngine/Include/Common/MessageStream.h`)

```cpp
class GameMessage : public MemoryPoolObject {
    enum Type { /* ~200 message types */ };

    // append typed arguments
    void appendIntegerArgument(Int arg);
    void appendRealArgument(Real arg);
    void appendBooleanArgument(Bool arg);
    void appendObjectIDArgument(ObjectID arg);
    void appendLocationArgument(const Coord3D& arg);
    void appendPixelArgument(const ICoord2D& arg);
    void appendPixelRegionArgument(const IRegion2D& arg);

    Int getPlayerIndex() const;   // which player issued it
};
```

### How to inject a command from headless code:

Append to `TheMessageStream` (it will be translated/dispatched to `TheCommandList`):
```cpp
GameMessage *msg = TheMessageStream->appendMessage(GameMessage::MSG_DO_MOVETO);
msg->appendLocationArgument(targetPos);
// or for a new game:
GameMessage *msg = TheMessageStream->appendMessage(GameMessage::MSG_NEW_GAME);
msg->appendIntegerArgument(GAME_SINGLE_PLAYER);
msg->appendIntegerArgument(DIFFICULTY_NORMAL);
msg->appendIntegerArgument(0);  // rank points
```

Or directly to `TheCommandList` to bypass translators (for network messages / replays):
```cpp
GameMessage *msg = TheCommandList->appendMessage(GameMessage::MSG_DO_MOVETO);
```

### Key command message types for AI training:
```
MSG_NEW_GAME                   — start a game (with mode, difficulty, rank args)
MSG_DO_MOVETO                  — move selection to location
MSG_DO_ATTACKMOVETO            — attack-move to location
MSG_DO_ATTACK_OBJECT           — attack specific object
MSG_DO_FORCE_ATTACK_GROUND     — bombard location
MSG_DOZER_CONSTRUCT            — build a structure
MSG_QUEUE_UNIT_CREATE          — produce a unit
MSG_QUEUE_UPGRADE              — research an upgrade
MSG_SELL                       — sell a structure
MSG_AREA_SELECTION             — select units in rectangle (pixel coords)
MSG_CREATE_SELECTED_GROUP      — define selection from object IDs
MSG_SET_RALLY_POINT            — set rally point
MSG_DO_SPECIAL_POWER_AT_LOCATION / MSG_DO_SPECIAL_POWER_AT_OBJECT
MSG_PURCHASE_SCIENCE           — buy a general's power
```

Note: All network commands use integer IDs starting at `MSG_BEGIN_NETWORK_MESSAGES = 1000` with explicit comment: *"there should be NO IFDEFS OF ANY KIND from here until MSG_END_NETWORK_MESSAGES"* — these are the only messages that go over the wire, and they are the ones that get replayed.

